http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/Naidu-promises-sports-academy-at-Kondavelagada/article13978701.ece

Chief Minister N. Chandrababu Naidu promised a sports academy at Kondavelagada in Nellimarla mandal where he inaugurated a weightlifting hall built at a cost of Rs. 45 lakh, on Saturday.He also promised to appoint a coach to train weightlifters and thanked GMR management for arranging Rs. 40-lakh worth equipment of international standard. The Chief Minister interacted with weightlifter Matsa Santoshi, who won medals in the Common Wealth Games, and encouraged her to repeat the same feat in the Olympics. The village was first in the news when Valluri Srinivasa Rao, a weightlifter, won a medal in Asian Games-2006 and later in CWG-2012.